HEADWORD: Fearnaught
<hw>Fear"naught`</hw> <pr>(f⟦emac⟧r"n⟦add⟧t`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A fearless person.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A stout woolen cloth of great thickness;
dreadnaught; also, a warm garment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fearsome</ent>⟦br⟧
